1. The "Monotonicity" Rule
With Positives only (and 0): The prefix sum is monotonic—it only goes up. This means if you move the right pointer, the sum always increases. If it gets too big, you move the left pointer to decrease it.
With Negatives: Adding an element can make the sum go up OR down. You lose that "predictable" direction, so a simple Sliding Window doesn't know whether to expand or shrink.

