3. The Only Exception: "Exact Equality"
If the question asks for Sum == K, you almost always use Prefix Sum + HashMap, regardless of whether the numbers are positive or negative.
Why? Because even with positive numbers, a sliding window only tells you if you are "above" or "below" a target; a HashMap finds the exact previous state needed to hit K instantly.
